由[[COVID-19|COVID-19]]引起的全球性破坏已经对环境和气候产生了许多影响。计划旅行因此出現大幅减少<ref name="bbcOverview1">{{cite web|title=Coronavirus: A visual guide to the pandemic|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-51235105|date=2020-03-28|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200327231951/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-51235105|archivedate=2020-03-27|last1=Team|first1=The Visual and Data Journalism|website=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|dead-url=no|accessdate=2020-08-08}}</ref>，使得许多地区的空气污染大幅下降。在中国，对城市地区的封锁和其他措施使碳排放量减少了25％<ref name="DIm4R">{{cite web|title=Analysis: Coronavirus has temporarily reduced China's CO2 emissions by a quarter|url=https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-02-19|last=Myllyvirta|first=Lauri|work=CarbonBrief|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304082845/https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|archive-date=2020-03-04}}</ref>，[[氮氧化物|氮氧化物]]排放量則减少了50％，<ref name="mdpi">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一位地球系统科学家估计，这可以在两个月内挽救至少77,000条生命。<ref name="GFEED">{{cite web|title=COVID-19 reduces economic activity, which reduces pollution, which saves lives.|url=http://www.g-feed.com/2020/03/covid-19-reduces-economic-activity.html|accessdate=2020-05-16|language=en|last1=Burke|first1=Marshall|website=Global Food, Environment and Economic Dynamics|archive-date=2020-05-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200519090754/http://www.g-feed.com/2020/03/covid-19-reduces-economic-activity.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="mcmahon">{{cite web|title=Study: Coronavirus Lockdown Likely Saved 77,000 Lives In China Just By Reducing Pollution|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-03-16|last=McMahon|first=Jeff|work=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317041245/https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|archive-date=2020-03-17|dead-url=no}}</ref> 其他对环境的积极影响包括国家政府系统控制的投资，以实现[[可持续发展|可持续]]的能源转化型以及与环境保护有关的其他目标，例如[[欧盟|欧盟]]的7年1万亿欧元预算提案和7500亿欧元的“下一代欧盟”恢复计划。 力求将欧盟支出的25％保留给气候友好型产业的支出。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Simon|first1=Frédéric|title='Do no harm': EU recovery fund has green strings attached|url=https://www.euractiv.com/section/energy-environment/news/do-no-harm-eu-recovery-fund-has-green-strings-attached/|accessdate=2020-06-04|work=www.euractiv.com|date=2020-05-27|archive-date=2020-07-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200716141631/https://www.euractiv.com/section/energy-environment/news/do-no-harm-eu-recovery-fund-has-green-strings-attached/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Carpenter|first1=Scott|title=As Europe Unveils 'Green' Recovery Package, Trans-Atlantic Rift On Climate Policy Widens|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottcarpenter/2020/05/27/as-europe-unveils-green-recovery-package-trans-atlantic-rift-on-climate-policy-widens/|accessdate=2020-06-04|work=Forbes|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210112054825/https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottcarpenter/2020/05/27/as-europe-unveils-green-recovery-package-trans-atlantic-rift-on-climate-policy-widens/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=France and Germany Bring European Recovery Fund Proposal to Table|url=https://southeusummit.com/europe/france/a-new-eu-rescue-fund-promises-solidarity-at-last/|accessdate=2020-06-04|date=2020-06-04|website=South EU Summit|archive-date=2021-01-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210118210052/https://southeusummit.com/europe/france/a-new-eu-rescue-fund-promises-solidarity-at-last/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

然而，疫情也掩盖了非法活动，例如在[[亚马逊雨林|亚马逊雨林]]的砍伐<ref name="Amazon12">{{cite news|title=Deforestation of Amazon rainforest accelerates amid COVID-19 pandemic|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/deforestation-amazon-rainforest-accelerates-amid-covid-19-pandemic/story?id=70526188|work=ABC News|date=2020-05-06|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708160111/https://abcnews.go.com/International/deforestation-amazon-rainforest-accelerates-amid-covid-19-pandemic/story?id=70526188|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Amazon2">{{cite news|title=Deforestation of the Amazon has soared under cover of the coronavirus|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/deforestation-amazon-has-soared-under-cover-coronavirus-n1204451|work=NBC News|date=2020-05-11|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711111421/https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/deforestation-amazon-has-soared-under-cover-coronavirus-n1204451|dead-url=no}}</ref> 和非洲的偷猎活动，<ref name="Poaching1">{{cite news|title=Conservationists fear African animal poaching will increase during COVID-19 pandemic|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/conservationists-fear-african-animal-poaching-increase-covid-19/story?id=70118142|work=ABC News|date=2020-04-14|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707161826/https://abcnews.go.com/International/conservationists-fear-african-animal-poaching-increase-covid-19/story?id=70118142|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="Poaching2">{{cite news|title='Filthy bloody business:' Poachers kill more animals as coronavirus crushes tourism to Africa|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/24/coronavirus-poachers-kill-more-animals-as-tourism-to-africa-plummets.html|work=CNBC|date=2020-04-24|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709025752/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/24/coronavirus-poachers-kill-more-animals-as-tourism-to-africa-plummets.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 阻碍了环境外交的努力，<ref name="UN">{{cite web|title=Cop26 climate talks postponed to 2021 amid coronavirus pandemic|url=https://www.climatechangenews.com/2020/04/01/cop26-climate-talks-postponed-2021-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/|date=2020-04-01|language=en|website=Climate Home News|access-date=2020-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404132430/https://www.climatechangenews.com/2020/04/01/cop26-climate-talks-postponed-2021-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/|archive-date=2020-04-04|dead-url=no}}</ref> 这会产生许多在经济上的不良性作用，并有许多人推测这将减慢对绿色能源技术的投资的发展进度。<ref name="9mMFi2">{{cite news|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/13/coronavirus-could-weaken-climate-change-action-hit-clean-energy.html|title=Coronavirus could weaken climate change action and hit clean energy investment, researchers warn|author=Newburger, Emma|publisher=[[CNBC|CNBC]]|date=2020-03-13|accessdate=2020-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200315223847/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/03/13/coronavirus-could-weaken-climate-change-action-hit-clean-energy.html|archive-date=2020-03-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 背景 ==
自人類踏入[[工業時代|工业化时代]]以来，便不斷產生愈來愈多的[[温室气体|温室气体]]，致使地球上的全球平均温度升高<ref>{{cite web|title=Air Pollution|url=https://www.who.int/airpollution/ambient/health-impacts/en/|accessdate=2020-06-23|publisher=WHO|last1=Mishra|first1=Anshuman|website=WORLD HEALTH ORGANISATION|archive-date=2020-12-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201210085824/https://www.who.int/airpollution/ambient/health-impacts/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref>，這直接导致了包括[[冰川|冰山融化]]和海平面上升等一系列的影响。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Is sea level rising?|url=https://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/sealevel.html|website=[[National_Oceanic_and_Atmospheric_Administration|National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]]|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200218172232/https://oceanservice.noaa.gov/facts/sealevel.html|archive-date=2020-02-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Climate Change|url=http://www.nationalgeographic.org/encyclopedia/climate-change/|date=2019-03-28|website=[[National_Geographic_Society|National Geographic Society]]|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231070002/https://www.nationalgeographic.org/encyclopedia/climate-change/|archive-date=2019-12-31|dead-url=no}}</ref> 人为影响下，人类活动以各种形式导致了环境的退化。{{citation needed|date=May 2020}}

先于[[COVID-19|COVID-19]]的大流行，一些针对大流行且应当被推荐给卫生局的措施包括隔离和保持社交距离。<ref>{{Citation|last1=Madhav|last4=Mulembakani|archive-date=2020-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323153254/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525302/|editor4-first=Prabhat|editor4-last=Jha|editor3-first=Susan|editor3-last=Horton|editor2-first=Hellen|editor2-last=Gelband|doi=10.1596/978-1-4648-0527-1_ch17|first6=Nathan|last6=Wolfe|first5=Edward|last5=Rubin|first4=Prime|first3=Mark|first1=Nita|last3=Gallivan|first2=Ben|last2=Oppenheim|access-date=2020-04-06|pmid=30212163|isbn=978-1-4648-0527-1|publisher=The International Bank for Reconstruction and Development / The World Bank|edition=3rd|editor-first=Dean T.|editor-last=Jamison|work=Disease Control Priorities: Improving Health and Reducing Poverty|url=http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK525302/|date=2017|title=Pandemics: Risks, Impacts, and Mitigation|dead-url=no}}</ref>

同样早于COVID-19大流行，研究人员认为经济活动的减少将有助于减小全球变暖以及空气和海洋污染，从而使环境慢慢恢复其原来的状态。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Anthropocentrism: More than Just a Misunderstood Problem|first1=Helen|last2=Washington|first2=Haydn|date=2018-02-01|journal=Journal of Agricultural and Environmental Ethics|issue=1|doi=10.1007/s10806-018-9711-1|volume=31|pages=109–127|language=en|issn=1573-322X|last3=Taylor|first3=Bron|last4=J Piccolo|first4=John|last1=Kopnina}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=The humanized Earth system (HES)|last=Rull|first=Valentí|date=2016-09-01|journal=The Holocene|issue=9|doi=10.1177/0959683616640053|volume=26|pages=1513–1516|language=en|bibcode=2016Holoc..26.1513R|issn=0959-6836}}</ref>

研究人员和官方人员还呼吁保护[[生物多样性|生物多样性]]，以将其作为COVID-19恢复政策的一部分。<ref>{{cite journal|title=COVID-19 recovery can benefit biodiversity|url=https://science.sciencemag.org/content/368/6493/838.2|first1=Ryan M.|last2=Sievers|first2=Michael|date=2020-05-22|journal=Science|accessdate=2020-05-22|issue=6493|doi=10.1126/science.abc1430|volume=368|pages=838–839|language=en|bibcode=2020Sci...368..838P|issn=0036-8075|pmid=32439784|last3=McClure|first3=Eva C.|last4=Turschwell|first4=Mischa P.|last5=Connolly|first5=Rod M.|s2cid=218836621|last1=Pearson|archive-date=2020-10-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201006061041/https://science.sciencemag.org/content/368/6493/838.2|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Letter: We call on leaders to put climate and biodiversity at the top of the agenda|url=https://www.ft.com/content/09d934ac-6f59-11ea-9bca-bf503995cd6f?src=rss|accessdate=2020-04-03|last1=Rodrigues|first1=CM|website=Financial Times|archive-date=2020-11-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201103073721/https://www.ft.com/content/09d934ac-6f59-11ea-9bca-bf503995cd6f?src=rss|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 空气质量 ==

因为疫情爆发对于旅游业和制造业的影响，很多地区以至于整个星球的空气污染都下降了。<ref name="mdpi2">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Watts|first1=Jonathan|last2=Kommenda|first2=Niko|date=2020-03-23|title=Coronavirus pandemic leading to huge drop in air pollution|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/23/coronavirus-pandemic-leading-to-huge-drop-in-air-pollution|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|access-date=2020-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200404031855/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/23/coronavirus-pandemic-leading-to-huge-drop-in-air-pollution|archive-date=2020-04-04|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Temporary reduction in daily global CO2 emissions during the COVID-19 forced confinement|first1=Corinne|last2=Jackson|first2=Robert B.|date=2020-05-19|journal=Nature Climate Change|issue=7|doi=10.1038/s41558-020-0797-x|volume=10|pages=647–653|language=en|issn=1758-6798|last3=Jones|first3=Matthew W.|last4=Smith|first4=Adam J. P.|last5=Abernethy|first5=Sam|last6=Andrew|first6=Robbie M.|last7=De-Gol|first7=Anthony J.|last8=Willis|first8=David R.|last9=Shan|first9=Yuli|s2cid=218693901|first11=Pierre|last11=Friedlingstein|first10=Josep G.|last10=Canadell|last1=Le Quéré}}</ref> 空气污染指数的下降不仅抑制了全球气候变化还减缓了COVID-19的传播，<ref>{{Cite news|last=editor|first=Damian Carrington Environment|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/apr/07/air-pollution-linked-to-far-higher-covid-19-death-rates-study-finds|title=Air pollution linked to far higher Covid-19 death rates, study finds|date=2020-04-07|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-04-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200409033624/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/apr/07/air-pollution-linked-to-far-higher-covid-19-death-rates-study-finds|archive-date=2020-04-09|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但目前还不清楚到底是哪一种空气污染起到的效果。能源与清洁空气研究中心报告称：各种为了抑制COVID-19传播的方法，例如隔离和禁行令，让中国的碳排放减少了25%。<ref name="DIm4R2">{{cite web|title=Analysis: Coronavirus has temporarily reduced China's CO2 emissions by a quarter|url=https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-02-19|last=Myllyvirta|first=Lauri|work=CarbonBrief|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304082845/https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|archive-date=2020-03-04}}</ref><ref name="mcmahon2">{{cite web|title=Study: Coronavirus Lockdown Likely Saved 77,000 Lives In China Just By Reducing Pollution|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-03-16|last=McMahon|first=Jeff|work=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317041245/https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|archive-date=2020-03-17|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在第一个月的封城中，相比2019年同期，中国大约少产生了2亿吨[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]。这主要是因为航班的减少，精炼油料的减少和煤炭消耗的减少导致的。<ref name="mcmahon4">{{cite web|title=Study: Coronavirus Lockdown Likely Saved 77,000 Lives In China Just By Reducing Pollution|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-03-16|last=McMahon|first=Jeff|work=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317041245/https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|archive-date=2020-03-17|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一个地球科学家估计这些减少的碳排放量拯救了至少77000人。<ref name="mcmahon3">{{cite web|title=Study: Coronavirus Lockdown Likely Saved 77,000 Lives In China Just By Reducing Pollution|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|accessdate=2020-03-16|date=2020-03-16|last=McMahon|first=Jeff|work=[[Forbes|Forbes]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200317041245/https://www.forbes.com/sites/jeffmcmahon/2020/03/16/coronavirus-lockdown-may-have-saved-77000-lives-in-china-just-from-pollution-reduction/|archive-date=2020-03-17|dead-url=no}}</ref> 然而来自战略与国际研究中心的Sarah Ladislaw认为因为经济下滑而导致的减排不应该被视为有益的。她指出当中国尝试回到之前的经济时，会因为贸易战和供给链断裂而加大它对环境的影响。<ref>{{cite web|title=The Global Impacts of the Coronavirus Outbreak|url=https://www.csis.org/analysis/global-impacts-coronavirus-outbreak|language=en|website=[[Center_for_Strategic_and_International_Studies|Center for Strategic and International Studies]]|access-date=2020-04-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200407202137/https://www.csis.org/analysis/global-impacts-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=2020-04-07|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在2020年的一月一号到三月十一日，[[欧洲空间局|欧洲空间局]]观测到因为[[意大利|意大利]]北部波河河谷的封城，从汽车，发电厂和工厂中产生的[[一氧化二碳|一氧化二碳]]有了一个非常醒目的下降。<ref name="StEML">{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-italy-pollution/air-pollution-clears-in-northern-italy-after-coronavirus-lockdown-satellite-shows-idUSKBN2102X4|title=Air pollution clears in northern Italy after coronavirus lockdown, satellite shows|last=Green|first=Matthew|agency=Reuters|date=2020-03-13|accessdate=2020-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200316105932/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-italy-pollution/air-pollution-clears-in-northern-italy-after-coronavirus-lockdown-satellite-shows-idUSKBN2102X4|archive-date=2020-03-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[美国国家航空航天局|美国国家航空航天局]]和[[欧洲空间局|欧洲空间局]]一直在监测[[二氧化氮|二氧化氮]]气体在[[中国|中国]][[COVID-19|COVID-19]]流行初期是如何显著下降的。COVID-19导致的经济放缓使污染水平大幅下降，特别是在中国[[武汉|武汉]]这样的城市，污染水平下降了25-40%。<ref name="mdpi3">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web|title=Airborne Nitrogen Dioxide Plummets Over China|url=https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/146362/airborne-nitrogen-dioxide-plummets-over-china|date=2020-02-28|language=en|website=earthobservatory.nasa.gov|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402162640/https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/images/146362/airborne-nitrogen-dioxide-plummets-over-china|archive-date=2020-04-02|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Analysis: Coronavirus temporarily reduced China's CO2 emissions by a quarter|url=https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|date=2020-02-19|language=en|website=Carbon Brief|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200304082845/https://www.carbonbrief.org/analysis-coronavirus-has-temporarily-reduced-chinas-co2-emissions-by-a-quarter|archive-date=2020-03-04|dead-url=no}}</ref> 美国航天局使用臭氧监测仪器(OMI)分析和观察[[臭氧层|臭氧层]]和污染物，如二氧化氮，[[气溶胶|气溶胶]]等等。这台仪器帮助美国航天局处理和解释由于全球各地封城而收到的数据。<ref>{{Cite web|title=NASA Aura OMI|url=https://aura.gsfc.nasa.gov/omi.html|date=|last=|first=|website=NASA Aura|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200303075331/https://aura.gsfc.nasa.gov/omi.html|archive-date=2020-03-03|access-date=}}</ref>
据美国国家航空航天局的科学家说，二氧化氮污染的下降始于中国武汉，并慢慢扩散到世界其他地方。下降的幅度也非常大，因为COVID0-19发生的时间正好是中国[[农历新年|农历新年]]的庆祝时间。<ref name="mdpi4">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref>在 这个节日期间，工厂和企业在1月的最后一周关闭以庆祝农历年节日。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Archived copy|url=https://chinesenewyear.net/|website=chinesenewyear.net|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229110431/https://chinesenewyear.net/|archive-date=2020-02-29|dead-url=no}}</ref>中 国二氧化氮的下降没有达到卫生部门认为可以接受的空气质量标准。空气中的其他污染物，如气溶胶排放仍然存在。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Earth Matters - How the Coronavirus Is (and Is Not) Affecting the Environment|url=https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2020/03/05/how-the-coronavirus-is-and-is-not-affecting-the-environment/|date=2020-03-05|language=en|website=earthobservatory.nasa.gov|access-date=2020-04-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200406235222/https://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2020/03/05/how-the-coronavirus-is-and-is-not-affecting-the-environment/|archive-date=2020-04-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>

一项由中美科学家共同参与的联合研究估计，与2020年1月1日至1日23日（武汉封城）相比，从2020年1月23日至2月9日，中国华东地区的[[氮氧化物|氮氧化物]]（NOx=NO+NO2）排放量减少了50%。<ref name="mdpi5">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref> 从2020年2月10日（返工日）到3月12日，排放量增加了26%，这表明在大多数省份重新允许企业开业之后，社会经济活动可能会增长。<ref name="mdpi6">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但 对COVID-19最有效的控制措施还需调查考究，以谋求最小的社会经济影响。<ref name="mdpi7">{{Cite journal|title=NOx Emission Reduction and Recovery during COVID-19 in East China|url=https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|first1=Ruixiong|last2=Zhang|first2=Yuzhong|date=April 2020|journal=Atmosphere|issue=4|doi=10.3390/atmos11040433|volume=11|pages=433|language=en|bibcode=2020Atmos..11..433Z|last3=Lin|first3=Haipeng|last4=Feng|first4=Xu|last5=Fu|first5=Tzung-May|last6=Wang|first6=Yuhang|last1=Zhang|s2cid=219002558|access-date=2020-05-06|via=|archive-date=2020-05-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522020712/https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4433/11/4/433|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 水质 ==
在[[威尼斯|威尼斯]]，运河里的水变得清澈透明，迎来了更大的水流量。<ref>{{cite news|title=Jellyfish seem swimming in Venice's canals|url=https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/jellyfish-venice/index.html|accessdate=2020-04-25|publisher=CNN|date=2020-04-23|archive-date=2020-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200627013936/https://www.cnn.com/travel/article/jellyfish-venice/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>水 体清澈度的提高是因为船只运输搅动起来的沉积物的重新沉淀，沿航道的空气污染也减少了。<ref name="63GlJ">{{cite web|title=As Italy quarantines over coronavirus, swans appear in Venice canals, dolphins swim up playfully|url=https://thehill.com/changing-america/sustainability/environment/488286-italys-coronavirus-lockdown-shows-what-nature|accessdate=2020-03-20|author=Srikanth, Anagha|date=2020-03-18|work=The Hill|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200319215915/https://thehill.com/changing-america/sustainability/environment/488286-italys-coronavirus-lockdown-shows-what-nature|archive-date=2020-03-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 野生动物 ==

因为全国流行疾病的影响，<ref name="smithsonian">{{cite news|last1=Korten|first1=Tristram|title=With Boats Stuck in Harbor Because of COVID-19, Will Fish Bounce Back?|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/fish-stop-covid-19-180974623/|accessdate=2020-04-24|publisher=Smithsonian Magazine|date=2020-04-08|archive-date=2020-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200617153054/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/fish-stop-covid-19-180974623/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 对鱼和鱼价格的需求都下降了，并且世界上的捕鱼船队大部分闲置。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Reiley|first1=Laura|title=Commercial fishing industry in free fall as restaurants close, consumers hunker down and vessels tie up|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2020/04/08/commercial-fishing-coronavirus/|accessdate=2020-04-25|work=[[The_Washington_Post|The Washington Post]]|date=2020-04-08|archive-date=2020-12-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201224164325/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/2020/04/08/commercial-fishing-coronavirus/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 德国科学家赖纳·弗洛斯（Rainer Froese）认为，因为捕捞量的急剧下降，鱼类的生物量将增加，并预计在欧洲水域，例如[[鲱鱼|鲱鱼]]的一些鱼类的生物量可以增加一倍。<ref name="smithsonian2">{{cite news|last1=Korten|first1=Tristram|title=With Boats Stuck in Harbor Because of COVID-19, Will Fish Bounce Back?|url=https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/fish-stop-covid-19-180974623/|accessdate=2020-04-24|publisher=Smithsonian Magazine|date=2020-04-08|archive-date=2020-06-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200617153054/https://www.smithsonianmag.com/science-nature/fish-stop-covid-19-180974623/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 截至2020年4月，水生恢复的迹象大部分还是少数的。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Millan Lombrana|first1=Laura|title=With Fishing Fleets Tied Up, Marine Life Has a Chance to Recover|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-17/with-fishing-fleets-tied-up-marine-life-has-a-chance-to-recover|accessdate=2020-04-25|publisher=Bloomberg Green|date=2020-04-17|archive-date=2020-07-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200723143637/https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-04-17/with-fishing-fleets-tied-up-marine-life-has-a-chance-to-recover|dead-url=no}}</ref>

正因为紧闭和旅行的限制使得人们呆在家里，一些动物出没在城市里。 [[海龟|海龟]]产卵在曾经避开的海滩（例如[[孟加拉湾|孟加拉湾海岸]]，因为人类干扰和[[光污染|光污染]]的降低。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.euronews.com/living/2020/04/25/while-you-stay-home-animals-roam-free-in-our-towns-and-cities |title=While you stay home, animals roam free in our towns and cities |accessdate=2020-08-08 |archive-date=2020-06-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626054356/https://www.euronews.com/living/2020/04/25/while-you-stay-home-animals-roam-free-in-our-towns-and-cities |dead-url=no }}</ref> 在美国，3月和4月，[[鹿|鹿]]，[[麋鹿|麋鹿]]，[[驼鹿|驼鹿]]，[[熊|熊]]，山狮等动物和车辆的致命碰撞下降了58％。<ref>{{cite news|last=Katz|first=Cheryl|date=2020-06-26|title=Roadkill rates fall dramatically as lockdown keeps drivers at home|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/2020/06/decline-road-kill-pandemic-lockdown-traffic/|work=[[National_Geographic|National Geographic]]|location=|access-date=2020-07-05|archive-date=2020-07-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200714222706/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/animals/2020/06/decline-road-kill-pandemic-lockdown-traffic/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[环境保护主义者|环境保护主义者]]预料非洲国家会经历一场巨大的的丛林肉偷猎活动。 自然保护协会的马特·布朗（Matt Brown）说到：“当人们没有其他收入替代选择时，我们的预测——正如我们在[[南非|南非]]所看到的——是价值高的产品像[[犀牛|犀牛角]]和[[象牙|象牙]]等被盗的可能性会增加。” <ref name="Poaching12">{{cite news|title=Conservationists fear African animal poaching will increase during COVID-19 pandemic|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/conservationists-fear-african-animal-poaching-increase-covid-19/story?id=70118142|work=ABC News|date=2020-04-14|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200707161826/https://abcnews.go.com/International/conservationists-fear-african-animal-poaching-increase-covid-19/story?id=70118142|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Poaching22">{{cite news|title='Filthy bloody business:' Poachers kill more animals as coronavirus crushes tourism to Africa|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/24/coronavirus-poachers-kill-more-animals-as-tourism-to-africa-plummets.html|work=CNBC|date=2020-04-24|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200709025752/https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/24/coronavirus-poachers-kill-more-animals-as-tourism-to-africa-plummets.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 另一方面，为了阻止人畜共患疾病的传播，加蓬决定禁止人类对[[蝙蝠|蝙蝠]]和[[穿山甲|穿山甲]]食用，因为COVID-19被认为是通过这些动物传播给人类。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Eating bats and pangolins banned in Gabon as a result of coronavirus pandemic|url=https://www.newsweek.com/eating-bats-pangolins-gabon-coronavirus-pandemic-1496329|date=2020-04-06|last=EDT|first=Rosie McCall On 4/6/20 at 11:18 AM|language=en|website=Newsweek|access-date=2020-05-19|archive-date=2020-05-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200529173436/https://www.newsweek.com/eating-bats-pangolins-gabon-coronavirus-pandemic-1496329|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 森林砍伐和重新造林 ==
由于疫情影响，人们减轻了对[[非法砍伐|非法砍伐森林]]的注意。通过卫星显示，在[[巴西|巴西]]境内，[[亚马逊雨林|亚马逊雨林]]的森林砍伐与基准水平相比激增了50％以上。<ref name="Amazon1">{{cite news|title=Deforestation of Amazon rainforest accelerates amid COVID-19 pandemic|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/deforestation-amazon-rainforest-accelerates-amid-covid-19-pandemic/story?id=70526188|work=ABC News|date=2020-05-06|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200708160111/https://abcnews.go.com/International/deforestation-amazon-rainforest-accelerates-amid-covid-19-pandemic/story?id=70526188|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="Amazon22">{{cite news|title=Deforestation of the Amazon has soared under cover of the coronavirus|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/deforestation-amazon-has-soared-under-cover-coronavirus-n1204451|work=NBC News|date=2020-05-11|accessdate=2020-08-08|archive-date=2020-07-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200711111421/https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/deforestation-amazon-has-soared-under-cover-coronavirus-n1204451|dead-url=no}}</ref> 与此同时，因疫情影响导致的失业率上升却促进了[[巴基斯坦|巴基斯坦国]]种植1千万棵树的5年计划，<ref>{{cite news|title=As a 'green stimulus' Pakistan sets virus-idled to work planting trees|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-pakistan-trees-fea/as-a-green-stimulus-pakistan-sets-virus-idled-to-work-planting-trees-idUSKCN22A369|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=Reuters|date=2020-04-28|language=en|archive-date=2020-07-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200705113010/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-pakistan-trees-fea/as-a-green-stimulus-pakistan-sets-virus-idled-to-work-planting-trees-idUSKCN22A369|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pakistan Hires Thousands of Newly-Unemployed Laborers for Ambitious 10 Billion Tree-Planting Initiative|url=https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/pakistan-hires-laborers-for-planting-10-billion-tree/|date=2020-04-30|agency=thegoodnewsnetwork|language=en|website=Good News Network|access-date=2020-05-02|publication-date=|archive-date=2020-06-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200620105559/https://www.goodnewsnetwork.org/pakistan-hires-laborers-for-planting-10-billion-tree/|dead-url=no}}</ref>相当于全世界每年流失的树木的数量。<ref>{{cite web|title=Earth has 3 trillion trees but they're falling at alarming rate|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-science-trees-idUSKCN0R21Z620150902|accessdate=2020-05-26|date=2015-09-02|language=en|website=Reuters|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111230631/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-science-trees-idUSKCN0R21Z620150902|dead-url=no}}</ref> 自从疫情影响以来，该计划边招募了大量失业人士。

== 碳排放 ==
2020年5月发表的一项研究发现：在4月初的封锁措施期间，全球每日[[温室气体|碳排放]]下降了17%，这可能导致每年碳排放下降高达7%，据研究人员称，这将是[[二战|二战]]以来最大的降幅。他们把这些减少主要归因于交通使用量和工业活动的减少。<ref>{{cite news|title=Carbon emissions fall 17% worldwide under coronavirus lockdowns, study finds|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/carbon-emissions-fall-coronavirus-lockdowns-worldwide/|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=www.cbsnews.com|archive-date=2020-07-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200703173040/https://www.cbsnews.com/news/carbon-emissions-fall-coronavirus-lockdowns-worldwide/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Global carbon emissions dropped 17 percent during coronavirus lockdowns, scientists say|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/carbon-emissions-dropped-17-percent-globally-amid-coronavirus-n1210331|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=NBC News|language=en|archive-date=2020-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722214301/https://www.nbcnews.com/science/environment/carbon-emissions-dropped-17-percent-globally-amid-coronavirus-n1210331|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但是，有人指出，由于工业活动比较有限，反弹可能会降低减少的排放量。<ref name="nationalgeographic12">{{cite news|title=Carbon emissions are falling sharply due to coronavirus. But not for long.|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/04/coronavirus-causing-carbon-emissions-to-fall-but-not-for-long/|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=Science|date=2020-04-03|language=en|archive-date=2020-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200623174129/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/04/coronavirus-causing-carbon-emissions-to-fall-but-not-for-long/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 然而，COVID-19封锁引起的社会变化——比如广泛的远程办公和虚拟会议技术的使用——可能会产生更持久的影响，而不仅仅是交通使用量的短期减少。<ref name="nationalgeographic13">{{cite news|title=Carbon emissions are falling sharply due to coronavirus. But not for long.|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/04/coronavirus-causing-carbon-emissions-to-fall-but-not-for-long/|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=Science|date=2020-04-03|language=en|archive-date=2020-06-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200623174129/https://www.nationalgeographic.com/science/2020/04/coronavirus-causing-carbon-emissions-to-fall-but-not-for-long/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=How scientific conferences will survive the coronavirus shock|url=https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-01521-3|first1=Giuliana|date=2020-06-02|journal=Nature|accessdate=2020-06-07|issue=7811|doi=10.1038/d41586-020-01521-3|volume=582|pages=166–167|language=en|pmid=32488188|last1=Viglione|s2cid=219284783|archive-date=2020-07-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200713154002/https://www.nature.com/articles/d41586-020-01521-3|dead-url=no}}</ref> 尽管如此，2020年5月大气中[[二氧化碳|二氧化碳]]的浓度还是有人类历史记录以来最高的。<ref name="nationalgeographic-plunge">{{cite news|title=Plunge in carbon emissions from lockdowns will not slow climate change|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|accessdate=2020-06-07|work=National Geographic|date=2020-05-29|language=en-gb|archive-date=2020-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626190237/https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|dead-url=no}}</ref> 能源和气候专家Constantine Samaras指出，“大流行是减少排放最糟糕的可能方式”，“技术、行为和结构上的改变是减少排放的最好也是唯一的方式”。<ref name="nationalgeographic-plunge2">{{cite news|title=Plunge in carbon emissions from lockdowns will not slow climate change|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|accessdate=2020-06-07|work=National Geographic|date=2020-05-29|language=en-gb|archive-date=2020-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626190237/https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|dead-url=no}}</ref>清华大学地球系统科学系副教授刘竹澄清说:“只有当我们在更长的时间内减少排放量，甚至更多的时候，我们才能看到大气中浓度的下降。” <ref name="nationalgeographic-plunge3">{{cite news|title=Plunge in carbon emissions from lockdowns will not slow climate change|url=https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|accessdate=2020-06-07|work=National Geographic|date=2020-05-29|language=en-gb|archive-date=2020-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626190237/https://www.nationalgeographic.co.uk/environment-and-conservation/2020/05/plunge-in-carbon-emissions-from-lockdowns-will-not-slow|dead-url=no}}</ref> 由于采取了针对COVID-19的措施，世界对[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]的需求下降了近10%。
据报道，许多能源经济学家认为，世界可能无法从危机中恢复过来。<ref name="guardian-fossilfuels">{{cite news|last1=Ambrose|first1=Jillian|title=Coronavirus crisis could cause $25tn fossil fuel industry collapse|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2020/jun/04/coronavirus-crisis-collapse-fossil-fuels-demand|accessdate=2020-06-06|work=The Guardian|date=2020-06-03|archive-date=2020-07-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200722140552/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2020/jun/04/coronavirus-crisis-collapse-fossil-fuels-demand|dead-url=no}}</ref>

