== 天气预报 ==
[[欧洲中期天气预报中心|欧洲中期天气预报中心]]（ECMWF）称，受疫情的影响已经有大量的商业用机停飞，这将大幅度影响天气预报的准确性。商业用机通过机上的设备收集和处理各类气象观测数据，是[[天气预报|天气预报]]和气候监测的重要信息来源。<ref>{{cite web|title=Drop in aircraft observations could have impact on weather forecasts|url=https://www.ecmwf.int/en/about/media-centre/news/2020/drop-aircraft-observations-could-have-impact-weather-forecasts|accessdate=2020-03-26|author=Press release|date=2020-03-24|work=European Center for Medium-Range Weather Forecasts|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200326005351/https://www.ecmwf.int/en/about/media-centre/news/2020/drop-aircraft-observations-could-have-impact-weather-forecasts|archive-date=2020-03-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 政治 ==
[[时代杂志|《时代》]]杂志强调了三种可能的风险：计划遵循2015年《巴黎协定》的2020年11月格拉斯哥会议的筹备工作被打乱；比起疫情，公众将全球变暖视为次重要优先项目，这减轻了政治人物的压力；而“重新启动”全球经济的愿望将导致额外的[[温室气体|温室气体]]生产过剩。然而，据国际能源署执行主任称，在COVID-19衰退期间油价下跌可能是摆脱[[化石燃料|化石燃料]]补贴的好机会。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Put clean energy at the heart of stimulus plans to counter the coronavirus crisis – Analysis|url=https://www.iea.org/commentaries/put-clean-energy-at-the-heart-of-stimulus-plans-to-counter-the-coronavirus-crisis|website=[[International_Energy_Agency|International Energy Agency]]|access-date=2020-04-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200402134500/https://www.iea.org/commentaries/put-clean-energy-at-the-heart-of-stimulus-plans-to-counter-the-coronavirus-crisis|archive-date=2020-04-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>

Carbon Tracker认为，中国不应该通过建设计划中的燃煤发电站来刺激经济，因为许多发电站的现金流量会为负，并且会变成搁浅的资产。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Political decisions, economic realities: The underlying operating cashflows of coal power during COVID-19|url=https://carbontracker.org/reports/political-decisions-economic-realities/|website=[[Carbon_Tracker|Carbon Tracker]]|access-date=2020-04-08|archive-date=2020-07-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200719112422/https://carbontracker.org/reports/political-decisions-economic-realities/|dead-url=no}}</ref>
大流行期间，美国特朗普政府中止了通过美国国家环境保护局（EPA）实施某些环境保护法律的工作。如果污染者可以声称这些违法行为是由大流行引起的，那么这将使他们无视某些环境法律。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Milman|first1=Oliver|last2=Holden|first2=Emily|title=Trump administration allows companies to break pollution laws during coronavirus pandemic|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/27/trump-pollution-laws-epa-allows-companies-pollute-without-penalty-during-coronavirus|accessdate=2020-05-30|work=The Guardian|date=2020-03-27|archive-date=2021-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210105153921/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/27/trump-pollution-laws-epa-allows-companies-pollute-without-penalty-during-coronavirus|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 预测的反弹效应 ==
排放[[温室气体|温室气体]]的企业和道路交通逐渐在COVID-19一级防范禁闭后复苏，但是人们认为这种复苏可能会增加而不是减少温室气体的排放。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2020/03/26/the-epidemic-provides-a-chance-to-do-good-by-the-climate|title=The epidemic provides a chance to do good by the climate|work=The Economist|access-date=2020-04-21|issn=0013-0613|archive-date=2021-01-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210114142650/https://www.economist.com/science-and-technology/2020/03/26/the-epidemic-provides-a-chance-to-do-good-by-the-climate|dead-url=no}}</ref> 以道路交通来说，这次的疫情对人们的生活和行为方式都有许多的影响，例如企业选择举办更多的线上会议和改变了更多的商业模式，而企业的这些改变间接的降低了道路交通排放的温室气体。另外，由于人们害怕公共场合会感染COVID-19，人们会在出行的时候会更多的依赖私人而不是公共交通工具，而这就会大大地增加温室气体的排放。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Environmental health and strengthening resilience to pandemics|url=http://www.oecd.org/coronavirus/policy-responses/environmental-health-and-strengthening-resilience-to-pandemics-73784e04/#section-d1e248|language=en|website=OECD|access-date=2020-05-14|archive-date=2020-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119120417/http://www.oecd.org/coronavirus/policy-responses/environmental-health-and-strengthening-resilience-to-pandemics-73784e04/#section-d1e248|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但是，疫情期间负责管理城市规划的工作者在一些城市也在创造新的自行车行驶道。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.euronews.com/2020/05/12/chain-reaction-commuters-and-cities-embrace-cycling-in-covid-19-era |title=Chain reaction: commuters and cities embrace cycling in COVID-19 era |accessdate=2020-08-08 |archive-date=2020-11-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113111626/https://www.euronews.com/2020/05/12/chain-reaction-commuters-and-cities-embrace-cycling-in-covid-19-era |dead-url=no }}</ref>

经济共同合作和发展组织推荐政府们继续去在疫情期间和结束之后执行现有的空气管理政策，并且给公共交通部门提供更多的资金支持。这会帮助他们提高容量和质量并且集中减少拥挤和促进更干净的设备。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Environmental health and strengthening resilience to pandemics|url=http://www.oecd.org/coronavirus/policy-responses/environmental-health-and-strengthening-resilience-to-pandemics-73784e04/#boxsection-d1e313|language=en|website=OECD|access-date=2020-05-14|archive-date=2020-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201119120417/http://www.oecd.org/coronavirus/policy-responses/environmental-health-and-strengthening-resilience-to-pandemics-73784e04/#boxsection-d1e313|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 心理与风险感知 ==
COVID-19导致的混乱以及带来的负面影响或许让一个灾难重重的未来变得近在咫尺，同时阻止危险发生的行动不再是个选择，而是必然。但是，疫情可能反向地让人们更加注重迫在眉睫的COVID-19，而非全球变暖在內这种长期威胁。<ref>{{cite news|title=The Guardian view on Brazil and the Amazon: don't look away {{!}} Editorial|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/jun/05/the-guardian-view-on-brazil-and-the-amazon-dont-look-away|accessdate=2020-06-09|work=The Guardian|date=2020-06-05|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201212202346/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/jun/05/the-guardian-view-on-brazil-and-the-amazon-dont-look-away|dead-url=no}}</ref>比爾蓋茲在2021年時說過氣候變遷將比疫情致命五倍。

== 對環境監測和預測的影響 ==
在[[歐洲中期天氣預報中心|歐洲中期天氣預報中心]]宣布，由於流行病飛機飛行在全球範圍內減少可能會影響天氣預報的準確性，理由是商業航空公司使用（ECMWF）飛機氣象資料中繼（AMDAR）作為一個整體的貢獻天氣預報的準確性。該ECMWF預測，AMDAR覆蓋率將由65％以上是由於商業航班的下降減少。

